carissa how to a girl's name is pronounced ka-crack-ah. it is latin and greek origin, and the importance of carissa is "beloved; grace". a simplified spelling of harisa of charis. it is also a useful form of face or carys. used by edmund spencer in his epic 1590 poem "the fairy queen". also the form of the charity.,the love,the grace, the goodness,the mercy, kind
A beloved, dear, deeply cared for woman

beloved,the face, as a girl's name is of latin origin, and the importance of the smiley face is "beloved". from the latin word "caritas", which means "love". pet form of face. also the shape of the carina. also the form of the charity. also the form of the kara.,love
A woman who acts like a man does

carla how to a girl's name is pronounced kar-lah. it is of old german origin, and the importance of carla is "free man". feminine of carl and short form of caroline. a european-sounding version of the many names of charles. a lot of favors, in the name of mixtures with different endings. see also carol, and chat. also the form of charlotte.,feminine form of charles,free man
